  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yapi Kredi Bank - Tu Renewable Energy Efficiency Loan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Investment of USD 60 million, in TRY, in a private placement mortgage covered  bond issuance by Yapi ve Kred Bankasi AS (YKB). It is complemented by USD 15  million of financing provided by the Clean Technology Fund (CTF) which is one  of the two Trust Funds under the Climate Investment Fund (CIF) Special Fund,  taking total aggregate investment to USD 75 million equivalent. The CIF was  established to provide scaled up financing in order to contribute to the  demonstration, deployment and transfer of low carbon technologies with  significant potential for long-term greenhouse gas emission savings.  The EBRD&apos;s investment is backed by a portfolio of residential mortgages and  was rated Baa1 by Moody&apos;s.</narrative>
  </description>
